How long does Nanoblading last?

Everyone's Nanoblading lasts differently, it depends on the following factors: 

First factor: it depends on the pigment.
For example, mineral pigments come out of the skin faster than organic pigments.

Second factor: It depends on the client's skin type. 
For example, on dry and thin skin, the pigment lasts longer than on oily or porous skin.

Third factor: it depends on the post-care
For example, if the client does not use cream, then after the procedure, the client needs to start using a SPF protective cream. This is the most important rule. 

To summarize all of the above, the result lasts from 1 to 2 years, but there is one exception. If nanoblading is done with carbon black base  pigment, the result lasts «forever» and looks grey , can only be removed by laser. 

We do use mineral base pigments, they usually disappears from the skin in 2-3 years copmplytitly.

Logo and branding are important elements in the success of a business.  A logo is the visual representation of a company’s identity and is the first thing that customers will see when they come into contact with a business.  It is the face of the company and is used to create a lasting impression.
It took me about half a year to create a new logo.  Business is a living organism and any business has its own energy.  That's where it all starts and that's where the energy is laid down.

In the new logo, every single detail has a hidden meaning:
Let's start with two triangles: the triangle is the most sustainable figure.  Sustainability!  In the energetic message, it is merkaba - divine protection and light.

The circle is a symbol of infinity, perfection and wholeness.
In sacred geometry, “a circle with a discovery in the center as a very ancient global symbol, a sacred sign that closes the One God, containing all creation.

The shape of a petal also has the shape of an eye, but there is a deeper meaning.  I was motivated to do this by an artist who was with me at the retreat.  She explained about her unique Art, see her work here @jaqbelcher , she said that her Art is the main figure of yoni, it's feminine, and I was inspired by her work.  I'm in a woman's business, and a woman's business is different from a man's business, so I would like to add a woman's touch.

Three dots.  The number three, the sacred number.  God loves the trinity.  God warns three times.  Nicola Tesla even stayed only on the third floor in hotels in his life and he attached great importance to numbers.
 
I'd love to tell you more, but for now this is a brief history of my logo.  I'd be happy to share everything I know about the beauty industry, self-realization in business and personal growth.  If something is of particular interest, share your ideas, let's discover it together!

THE BIGGEST FAILURE …I promised you 

My biggest failure was to open two  new studios at the same time during a difficult time for any business after the pandemic. This was a huge risk and I paid the price for it, losing a lot of money and energy.  To make matters worse, I was going through a divorce with my business partner at the same time. To manage 3 locations only with one business partner and in 3 different states, never will do it again 😂

 The situation was complicated and I had to make a lot of difficult decisions.  I had to make sure that the business was able to survive and that my partner and I could still work together.  It was a stressful time, but I was able to find a way to make it work.  I was able to find a way to keep the business afloat and to come out of the situation with maturity👌

 I am a master of getting out of difficult situations and I have gone through a deep transformation because of this experience.  Not only this situation, obviously. I have learned a lot and I am now wiser and more thoughtful when it comes to making decisions.  If you ever find yourself in a difficult situation, I urge you to be wise and to do everything thoughtfully. 

Love you all❤️ Thanks for comments 😘

My first wins in the beauty industry were at the eyelash extension championship exactly 10 years ago. I was a young girl with big dreams, determined to take all three first places and leave to conquer America. Despite my ambitions, I only managed to take two of the top spots. It was this success that gave me the courage to move to the USA, where I knew the market for volume building was empty. 

Ten years later, I am proud to say that I have achieved my goals and made a name for myself in the American beauty industry. Participating in the championships was an important part of my success, as it allowed me to hone my skills and win prizes that gave me a huge jump in my career. 

Now, I am looking to make a breakthrough in my career and take my skills to the next level. With the American beauty market  we all can achieve our goals and dreams . Participating in championships and events is an important part of this journey, and I am excited to see what the future holds.

A lot of you got upset with the fact that Microblading is dead. Well it’s time to face it. And it’s definitely dead for me. 
 
I am an artist with years of experience, and, just like others, I sure worked in this technique: it was popular, it was new, it was better then tattoo brows.
 
Very quick I came to realize only certain clients are actually good candidates for this procedure. It made me very upset so I started to look for alternative to give my clients the best quality of service and fantastic healed results. 
 
As soon as I discovered nanoblading, that was it for me. 
 
We all see these terrible cases of removing and covering up old microblading. I said no to it. 
 
By the way, tattoo brows has been around for ages, but we not running around promoting it, do we ? Same goes to microblading - there is something newer, better on the market. Sooner or later the majority will accept it. 
 
I get it, a lot of artists don't like the machine hairstrokes, because it's extremely hard to master this technique, and they don't want to learn and put their energy and time into this path.
 
But let’s be honest ! Machine hair strokes are our future + classic technique like powdered brows will always be around. Tested for years. I wouldn’t just say that if I'm not 100% sure about it.

NANOBLADING PREPS
 
It is my priority to stay up to date with nanoblading procedures for the best results, so I am constantly analyzing the process before, during and after & monitoring the outcome. I recently updated my recommendations of preparation for your nanoblading appointment. Read & save it to make sure your have the best experience with me 🖤
 
Before the procedure:

	1.	72 hours Prior to your procedure, avoid alcohol & aspirin / ibuprofen & any vitamins that may thin your blood
	2.	Don’t get a facial / chemical peels at least 2 weeks prior to treatment
	3.	Don’t sunbathe, tan, or workout the day of your procedure
	4.	No botox at least 2 weeks before the treatment.
	5.	Procedure cannot be performed during the pregnancy or breastfeeding period
	6.	Don’t wax or tweeze your eyebrows a week prior
	7.	If you take any medications, consult with your care provider prior to procedure
	8.	If you have any serious illnesses, consult with your care provider prior to procedure
	9.	Last, but not least - I DO allow my clients to have coffee on the morning of the procedure 😉 ☕️ but let’s keep it at 1 cup!

If you think I went to Burning Man to party - you are wrong. I went there knowing another transformation was inevitable. You know by now I am into transformations )
 
Day one, I was cruising around Black Rock City and have discovered a place with the strongest energy that just pulls you in ⚡️⚡️⚡️I was drown to it and just couldn’t NOT come inside!
 
It appeared to be a Temple, where people come to let go of their past, loved ones, pain, memories - everything that holds you down. 

As soon you step inside, you feel that unreal energy running  through your body, guiding you through the space. Walls inside were all cover with names and pictures of people and faces. There were lots of people inside, crying, saying goodbyes. 

The place felt so powerful, I knew I needed to come back there tomorrow and let go of my rich and heavy past.
 
The next morning, I picked a very special outfit  and 
started my journey called FORGIVENESS. 

I had my book with me and I read it inside of the Temple. Inside the book - my path, my way, my story of becoming who I AM today. Going through those pages brought me to tears: I could feel how far have I gone and I was ready to leave everything behind at that moment. 

I cried for 2 hours and I couldn’t stop until I was able to forgive MYSELF. 

Forgiving yourself equals to letting  your past go. And it is never easy. I’ve been working on this for over a year and it finally felt like I’m done with it. It doesn’t have power over me anymore. 
 
I forgave everyone and let everyone go. 
Everyone who were by my side, no matter what, through all my pain and tears, I love you, I forgive you, please forgive me, too. 
 
Everything that happened to me made me stronger and my soul - bigger. Without all of you, there would be no NEW ME.

That was hands down one of the most important moments @ BurningMan. But one of the many ) 
 
Keep sharing ?

P.S. That Temple was burned to the ground, together with everything inside, including my book. It’s pretty symbolic, don’t you think ? You could still get your copy, even though I set mine on fire 🔥 link in bio

WHY BROW TINT ? 

Brow tint was the very first product of the SOULU line, and ⬇️⬇️⬇️
 
… there is one thing you need to always remember about permanent brows: PMU is not a solution to even out the color of your eyebrow’s hair. If your natural color is lighter than the brows you get, or if you have a few grays in them - you’re going to need to eventually color your brows. And the brow tint is a perfect solution for this!
 
It’s also perfect for those who want their brows to look brighter, and those, who is yet hesitant about permanent make up but wants that well groomed look. 
 
My client or not - literally everyone needs it! Especially, if it’s easy to apply and can be done safely at home. 
 
And this is why I knew I have to start with this product 🔥❤️
